OL,6,F"Our latest research found that more
OL,7,Fthan half of teachers polled worked
OL,8,Fmore than 50 hours a week, with some
OL,9,Fworking more than 70 hours.
OL,11,F"This is unsustainable and
OL,12,Funacceptable. World-class education
OL,13,Fcannot be built off the backs of over-
OL,14,Fworked and underpaid teachers and
OL,15,Fheadteachers."
OL,17,FDaniel Kebede, general secretary of
OL,18,Fthe National Education Union, said:
OL,19,F"The Government has shot itself in the
OL,20,Ffoot by failing to tackle working
OL,21,Fhours for so long.
