OL,6,FTUC general secretary Paul Nowak said:
OL,7,F"We're encouraging every worker to
OL,8,Ftake their lunchbreak and finish on
OL,9,Ftime today, and we know that the best
OL,10,Femployers will support them doing that.
OL,12,F"Most workers don't mind putting in
OL,13,Fextra hours from time to time, but
OL,14,Fthey should be paid for it.
OL,16,F"Part of the problem is that some
OL,17,Femployers fail to record the overtime
OL,18,Fstaff do and when they don't record
OL,19,Fit, they don't pay it.
